  "title": "“STOP OPENCLAW.”",
  "content": "<div><div class=\"duet--layout--entry-body _9f4de40\"><a class=\"p0svkz0 p492sh1\" href=\"https://www.theverge.com/news/872091/openclaw-moltbot-clawdbot-ai-agent-news\"><svg class=\"p0svkz4\" width=\"6\" height=\"10\"><path></path></svg><div><div class=\"p0svkz2\"><p class=\"p0svkz3 _1pm20r51 _1pm20r50\"><span>OpenClaw: all the news about the trending AI agent</span></p></div><p class=\"p0svkz1\">See all Stories</p></div></a><div class=\"duet--content-cards--content-card duet--content-cards--quick-post yy0d3l6\"><div class=\"yy0d3l3 yy0d3l0\"><div class=\"yy0d3l7\"><div class=\"_1t4tcr90\"><div class=\"wn1wvof wn1wvo0\"><p class=\"duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph _1ymtmqpi _17nnmdy1 _17nnmdy0 _1xwtict1\">That’s the WhatsApp message Meta safety and alignment researcher Summer Yue <a href=\"https://x.com/summeryue0/status/2025774069124399363\">sent her AI agent</a> while “watching it speedrun deleting [her] inbox.” Despite the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/news/874011/openclaw-ai-skill-clawhub-extensions-security-nightmare\">various</a> reasons <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/ai-artificial-intelligence/881574/cline-openclaw-prompt-injection-hack\">not to connect OpenClaw</a> to your actual data, apparently, she felt confident based on its results with her toy inbox and moved it to her actual Gmail.</p></div><div class=\"wn1wvof\"><p class=\"duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph _1ymtmqpi _17nnmdy1 _17nnmdy0 _1xwtict1\">Unfortunately, the AI bot “lost” her instruction not to take action without checking first.</p></div></div><div class=\"wn1wvoc\"><div><div class=\"_1ymtmqpj\"><div class=\"\"><div class=\"duet--media--content-warning ucljxw0\"><div class=\"duet--article--image-gallery-image kqz8fh0\" id=\"dmcyOmltYWdlOjg4MzI0NQ==\"><figure><img srcset=\"https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/02/HBz-x6nbAAAOqt7.jpg?quality=90&amp;strip=all&amp;cr